Cobra Mobile - Privacy Policy
Updated 10th January, 2024.
Cobra Mobile is committed to protecting our users ("you", "your") privacy.
This website ("the Website") is owned and operated by Cobra Mobile Limited ("
we
", "
us
", "
our
").
This privacy policy is for any Cobra Mobile provided application ("
game
", "
application
") and services provided as part of.
DATA COLLECTION
Cobra Mobile collects certain game play usage related data for the purpose of improving our games and related services. This helps us to understand what players are doing and what parts of our games are working and not working. This data is collected anonymously and through Third Party Services (see below). If you do not wish to share any game play related data you can switch this off at any time in the settings menu via the "Data Usage" option.
Where applicable, the Data Usage option in the Application allows you to disable all Data Collection. Data Usage/Data collection is only relevant to our Mobile, Tablet and Smart TV applications.
DATA SHARING
We do not share any collected data with any other party and any data we collect is stored safely.
DATA TRANSFER
Cobra Mobile reserves the right to transfer any currently held data in the event that,
∙ It is required to by law
∙ When we believe in good faith that disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, protect your safety or the safety of others, investigate fraud, or respond to a government request.
∙ If Cobra Mobile is involved in a company merger, acquisition, sale or change of ownership.
THIRD PARTY SERVICE
At present the Application may use a third party service from "
Unity Ads
", "
AppLovin
", "
Flurry
", "
